The paper proposes a Siamese neural network for extracting acquisition-invariant feature vectors from MRI-scanner data, which is a problem related to computer vision (CV). The use of neural networks for feature extraction and classification also suggests that the paper could belong to the machine learning (LG) or artificial intelligence (AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of simulated data, which could suggest a focus on numerical analysis (NE), and the use of patient data suggests a focus on multimedia (MM).
